32	def _format_version_specifiers(spec: Set[str]) -> Set[str]:
33	    return set([part for v in [v.split(",") for v in spec if v] for part in v if "!=" not in part])

12	code = """
13	import asyncio
14	import datetime
15	import os
16	
17	import %(module)s as elasticsearch
18	from %(module)s import %(class)s as AsyncClient
19	
20	ELASTICSEARCH_CONFIG = {
21	  "host": os.getenv("TEST_ELASTICSEARCH_HOST", "127.0.0.1"),
22	  "port": int(os.getenv("TEST_ELASTICSEARCH_PORT", 9200)),
23	}
24	ES_INDEX = "ddtrace_index"
25	ES_URL = "http://%%s:%%d" %% (ELASTICSEARCH_CONFIG["host"], ELASTICSEARCH_CONFIG["port"])
26	
27	async def main():
28	    es = AsyncClient(hosts=[ES_URL])
29	    if elasticsearch.__version__ >= (8, 0, 0):
30	        await es.options(ignore_status=400).indices.create(index=ES_INDEX)
31	        await es.options(ignore_status=[400, 404]).indices.delete(index=ES_INDEX)
32	    else:
33	        await es.indices.create(index=ES_INDEX, ignore=400)
34	        await es.indices.delete(index=ES_INDEX, ignore=[400, 404])
35	    await es.close()
36	
37	asyncio.run(main())
38	"""

>> Issue: [B824:url_found] url_found
   Severity: Medium   Confidence: Medium

   More Info: https://bandit.readthedocs.io/en/latest/plugins/b824_url_found.html
56	def test_processor_atexit(ddtrace_run_python_code_in_subprocess):
57	    code = """
58	import pytest
59	import sys
60	import time
61	
62	from ddtrace.internal.datastreams.processor import DataStreamsProcessor
63	from ddtrace.internal.atexit import register_on_exit_signal
64	
65	def fake_flush(*args, **kwargs):
66	    print("Fake flush called")
67	
68	_exit = False
69	def set_exit():
70	    global _exit
71	    _exit = True
72	
73	def run_test():
74	    processor = DataStreamsProcessor("http://localhost:8126")
75	    processor._flush_stats_with_backoff = fake_flush
76	    processor.stop(5)  # Stop period processing/flushing
77	
78	    now = time.time()
79	    processor.on_checkpoint_creation(1, 2, ["direction:out", "topic:topicA", "type:kafka"], now, 1, 1)
80	    now_ns = int(now * 1e9)
81	    bucket_time_ns = int(now_ns - (now_ns % 1e10))
82	    aggr_key = (",".join(["direction:out", "topic:topicA", "type:kafka"]), 1, 2)
83	    assert processor._buckets[bucket_time_ns].pathway_stats[aggr_key].full_pathway_latency.count == 1
84	
85	    counter = 0
86	    while counter < 500 and not _exit:
87	        counter += 1
88	        time.sleep(0.1)
89	
90	register_on_exit_signal(set_exit)
91	run_test()
92	"""
93	
94	    env = os.environ.copy()
